    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "VIOgvcdDdZAH"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Understanding Attention: Residual Stream Geometry\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook implements the foundational analysis of transformer residual streams based on the framework from \"A Mathematical Framework for Transformer Circuits\"\n",
        "\n",
        "### Core Implementations:\n",
        "1.  Residual Stream as Communication Channel\": The residual stream is a higher dimensional space where all layers read and write. It has no privileged basis and is deeply linear.\n",
        "\n",
        "2. **Residual Stream Recurrence**:\n",
        "   $$x^{(l)} = x^{(l-1)} + f^{(l)}(x^{(l-1)})$$\n",
        "   where $f^{(l)}$ is the $l$-th layer (attention + MLP). The final output is:\n",
        "   $$x^{(L)} = x^{(0)} + \\sum_{l=1}^{L} f^{(l)}(x^{(l-1)})$$\n",
        "\n",
        "3. **Virtual Weights**: Because the residual stream is linear, we can think of\n",
        "   implicit \"virtual weights\" connecting any pair of layers:\n",
        "   $$W_{virtual}^{(i \\to j)} = W_I^{(j)} W_O^{(i)}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "4. **Subspace Bandwidth**: The residual stream has $d_{model}$ dimensions.\n",
        "   Attention heads operate on $d_{head}$ dimensions (typically 64), which is\n",
        "   much smaller. This means attention operates in a lower-dimensional subspace\n",
        "   of the residual stream.\n",
        "\n",
        "5. **Attention Head as Information Movement**:\n",
        "   $$h(x) = (A \\otimes W_{OV}) \\cdot x$$\n",
        "   where $A$ is the attention pattern and $W_{OV} = W_O W_V$ is the\n",
        "   output-value circuit.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        " $d_{head} = 64 \\ll d_{model} = 768$. Each attention head operates in a\n",
        "subspace that is only 8.3% of the full residual stream dimension. This is the\n",
        "key insight: **attention is a low-rank operation within the high-dimensional\n",
        "residual stream**."
      ]
    },
