      "source": [
        "### Cachine Forward Pass Activations\n",
        "\n",
        "The residual stream at layer $l$ is:\n",
        "$$x^{(l)} = x^{(0)} + \\sum_{i=1}^{l} \\text{Attn}^{(i)}(x^{(i-1)}) + \\sum_{i=1}^{l} \\text{MLP}^{(i)}(x^{(i-1)})$$\n",
        "\n",
        "TransformerLens allows us to cache all intermediate activations. We can inspect:\n",
        "- `resid_pre`: Residual stream BEFORE the layer's attention (input to layer $l$)\n",
        "- `resid_mid`: Residual stream AFTER attention, BEFORE MLP\n",
        "- `resid_post`: Residual stream AFTER the full layer (output of layer $l$)\n",
        "\n",
        "For an attention-only model (simplified view):\n",
        "$$x^{(l)}_{pre} = x^{(l-1)}_{post}$$\n",
        "$$x^{(l)}_{mid} = x^{(l)}_{pre} + \\sum_{h} \\text{AttnHead}_h(x^{(l)}_{pre})$$\n",
        "$$x^{(l)}_{post} = x^{(l)}_{mid} + \\text{MLP}(x^{(l)}_{mid})$$\n"
      ]
    },
