        "id": "CpU8Q3W7hhN3"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Experiment 1.1: Norm Trajectory Analysis\n",
        "\n",
        "The residual stream norm grows with depth due to cumulative additions:\n",
        "$$\\|x^{(l)}\\| \\approx \\|x^{(l-1)}\\| + \\text{contribution from layer } l$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Hypothesis-1: Norms grow monotonically, with early layers contributing more\n",
        "to the growth than later layers (where representations may stabilize).\n",
        "\n",
        "We compute $\\|x^{(l)}_t\\|_2$ for each token position $t$ and layer $l$.\n",
        "\"\"\""
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 81,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "G3W7gh7Hhb2D"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def compute_residual_norms(cache, n_layers, batch_idx=0):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Compute L2 norms of residual stream at each layer.\n",
        "    Returns: dict with 'pre', 'mid', 'post' norms, each shape [n_layers, n_tokens]\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    norms = {'pre': [], 'mid': [], 'post': []}\n",
        "\n",
        "    for l in range(n_layers):\n",
        "        # resid_pre: before attention\n",
        "        resid_pre = cache[f'blocks.{l}.hook_resid_pre'][batch_idx]  # [n_tokens, d_model]\n",
        "        # resid_mid: after attention, before MLP\n",
        "        resid_mid = cache[f'blocks.{l}.hook_resid_mid'][batch_idx]  # [n_tokens, d_model]\n",
        "        # resid_post: after full layer\n",
        "        resid_post = cache[f'blocks.{l}.hook_resid_post'][batch_idx]  # [n_tokens, d_model]\n",
        "\n",
        "        norms['pre'].append(torch.norm(resid_pre, dim=-1).cpu().numpy())\n",
        "        norms['mid'].append(torch.norm(resid_mid, dim=-1).cpu().numpy())\n",
        "        norms['post'].append(torch.norm(resid_post, dim=-1).cpu().numpy())\n",
        "\n",
        "    return {k: np.stack(v) for k, v in norms.items()}"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 82,
      "metadata": {
