      "source": [
        "Findings:\n",
        "1. Residual Stream Trajectory:\n",
        "All three streams shows steady trajectory fom layer 0-11.\n",
        "    - MLP Contribution: resid_post(after MLP) consistently exceeds resid_mid (after attention) indicating MLP adds more to the stream than attention.\n",
        "    - Attention Contribution: GAP between resid_pre and resid_mid is small , showing that attention writes relatively little.\n",
        "    - Late layer surge: Sharpest norm growth seen after layer8.\n",
        "\n",
        "2. Residual Stream Norm Heatmap:\n",
        "    - Early Layers: Near-zero norms (darkpurple) across all token positions in layer 0-9\n",
        "    - Late-layer spike : Layer 10-11 shows dramatically elevated layer norms\n",
        "    - Token variation : Last token the and a few others shows the highest norm in deep layers.\n",
        "    - Overall : most computation and norm accumulation happens in the final 2 layers\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nq5ofFt8k9fq"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Experiment 1.2: Performing Single Value Decomposition in the Residual Stream\n",
        "\n",
        "The residual stream at each layer can be viewed as a stacked matrix.\n",
        "\n",
        "$X^{(l)} \\in \\mathbb{R}^{T \\times d_{model}}$ (token positions × model dimension)\n",
        "\n",
        "Applying SVD: $X^{(l)} = U^{(l)} \\Sigma^{(l)} (V^{(l)})^T$\n",
        "\n",
        "$V^{(l)}$ describe the **subspace structure** of the\n",
        "residual stream at layer $l$. We can analyze:\n",
        "1. Singular value spectra (how \"concentrated\" the representation is)\n",
        "2. Subspace overlap between layers (principal angles)\n",
        "3. Variance compression (how many dimensions are actually needed)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
