      "source": [
        "### Experiment 1.3 : Subspace Overlap Between Layers\n",
        "\n",
        "Principal angles between subspaces $V^{(l_1)}$ and $V^{(l_2)}$ reveal how\n",
        "the residual stream's \"basis of meaning\" evolves across layers.\n",
        "\n",
        "We compute the overlap score: $\\|V^{(l_1)T} V^{(l_2)}\\|_F$\n",
        "\n",
        "Hypothesis: Adjacent layers have higher overlap than distant layers."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 87,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8VHok2dDm6uW"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def compute_subspace_overlap(svd_results, n_layers, top_k=2):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Compute Frobenius norm of V_l1^T @ V_l2 for top-k singular vectors.\n",
        "    Returns overlap matrix [n_layers, n_layers]\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    overlap = np.zeros((n_layers, n_layers))\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i in range(n_layers):\n",
        "        for j in range(n_layers):\n",
        "            V_i = svd_results[i]['V'][:, :top_k]  # [d_model, top_k]\n",
        "            V_j = svd_results[j]['V'][:, :top_k]  # [d_model, top_k]\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Frobenius norm of overlap\n",
        "            overlap_ij = np.linalg.norm(V_i.T @ V_j, 'fro')\n",
        "            # Normalize by max possible (top_k)\n",
        "            overlap[i, j] = overlap_ij / top_k\n",
        "\n",
        "    return overlap"
      ]
    },
