      "source": [
        "### Findings:\n",
        "1. Top-1 Accuracy: Flat 0.1 until layer 10, then jumps at 0.5 at layer 11 : Prediction only crystallizes at the very last layer.\n",
        "2. Entropy: Slowly decreases 0-6 then spikes at layer 11: Model becomes uncertain right before the ouput, consistent with distributing pobability acorss plausible next tokens.\n",
        "3. True Token Rank : Worsens lauer 0-11 and then best at layer 11 : Correct token is actively deprioritized mid-network recovered only at the end.\n",
        "4. True Token Prob: Noisy mid-network , jumps to 0.15 at layer 11: Probability mass on correct tokens is almost entirely a last-layer phenomenon\n",
        "\n",
        "> Logit Lens quality should improve monotonically however in our case improves abruptly at the final layer. This is a known pattern in smaller transformers called ***Abrupt Decision Transition*** the model doesnt gradually assemble predictions, it holds representations in an internal basis and converts to vocabulary space only at the end.\n",
        "\n",
        "> Meaning: In smaller transformer (and even layer-pruned larger LLMs), we frequently observe a sharp and a non-monotonic rather than gradual slope.\n",
        "- Layer 0-10 : The Silent Phase: The model is doing the heavy lifting of context gathering, semantic routing and abstraction deduction. It is actively processing the concepts but in its own native, highly-dimensional geometric space.\n",
        "- Layer 11 : The model abruptly forces this internal concept to align with the token vocabulary."
      ]
    },
