      "source": [
        "## Core Insight: Attention Operates in a Lower-Dimensional Subspace\n",
        "\n",
        "From the paper:\n",
        "> \"An attention head is really applying two linear operations, A and $W_O W_V$,\n",
        "> which operate on different dimensions and act independently.\"\n",
        "\n",
        "The OV circuit: $W_{OV} = W_O W_V \\in \\mathbb{R}^{d_{model} \\times d_{model}}$\n",
        "\n",
        "But since $W_V \\in \\mathbb{R}^{d_{model} \\times d_{head}}$ and\n",
        "$W_O \\in \\mathbb{R}^{d_{head} \\times d_{model}}$, the rank of $W_{OV}$ is at most\n",
        "$d_{head} \\ll d_{model}$.\n",
        "\n",
        "This means:\n",
        "- Each head can only read from a $d_{head}$-dimensional subspace of the residual stream\n",
        "- Each head can only write to a $d_{head}$-dimensional subspace of the residual stream\n",
        "- The full residual stream ($d_{model}$) is the \"communication channel\" that aggregates\n",
        "  outputs from all heads"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 98,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "MPK8rb6RxNyr"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def analyze_ov_circuits(model):\n",
        "  \"\"\"\n",
        "  Compute W_OV = W_0 and W_V for all heads and analyze their rank structure.\n",
        "  \"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "  n_layers = model.cfg.n_layers\n",
        "  n_heads = model.cfg.n_heads\n",
        "\n",
        "  ov_ranks = np.zeros((n_layers,n_heads))\n",
        "  ov_singular_values = {}\n",
        "\n",
        "  for l in range (n_layers):\n",
        "    for h in range (n_heads):\n",
        "      W_O = model.W_O[l,h]\n",
        "      W_V = model.W_V[l,h]\n",
        "      W_OV = (W_V @ W_O).detach().cpu().numpy()\n",
        "\n",
        "      U, S, Vh = np.linalg.svd(W_OV)\n",
        "\n",
        "      p = S**2 / np.sum(S**2)\n",
        "      cumvar = np.cumsum(S**2)/np.sum(S**2)\n",
        "      eff_rank = np.argmax(cumvar >=0.95)+1\n",
        "      ov_ranks[l, h] = eff_rank\n",
        "      ov_singular_values[(l, h)] = S\n",
        "  return ov_ranks, ov_singular_values\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 100,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9seSmQzq2jDf"
      },
