      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Residual Stream Decomposition\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_SaRZz5i9Pmf"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Decomposing the Residual Stream: What Each Layer Contributes\n",
        "\n",
        "The final residual stream is the sum of all contributions:\n",
        "$$x^{(L)} = x^{(0)} + \\sum_{l=1}^{L} \\Delta x^{(l)}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where $\\Delta x^{(l)} = \\text{Attn}^{(l)} + \\text{MLP}^{(l)}$ is what layer $l$ adds.\n",
        "\n",
        "The triangle inequality tells us:\n",
        "$$\\left\\|x^{(0)} + \\sum_{l=1}^{L} \\Delta x^{(l)}\\right\\| \\leq \\|x^{(0)}\\| + \\sum_{l=1}^{L} \\|\\Delta x^{(l)}\\|$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The **cumulative contribution norm** (sum of magnitudes) is an upper bound.\n",
        "The actual residual stream norm grows more slowly because contributions can:\n",
        "- **Align** (cosine similarity ≈ 1): norms add constructively\n",
        "- **Cancel** (cosine similarity ≈ -1): norms partially cancel\n",
        "- **Orthogonal** (cosine similarity ≈ 0): norms add in quadrature\n",
        "\n",
        "We analyze both the per-layer magnitudes AND the geometric alignment between\n",
        "consecutive contributions to understand the \"geometry of addition\" in the\n",
        "residual stream.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4Vx1S-2t9USv"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def compute_layer_contributions(cache, model, batch_idx=0):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Compute per-layer additions to the residual stream.\"\"\"\n",
        "    contributions = {'attn': [], 'mlp': [], 'total': []}\n",
        "\n",
        "    for l in range(model.cfg.n_layers):\n",
        "        resid_pre = cache[f'blocks.{l}.hook_resid_pre'][batch_idx]\n",
        "        resid_mid = cache[f'blocks.{l}.hook_resid_mid'][batch_idx]\n",
        "        attn_contrib = (resid_mid - resid_pre).cpu().numpy()\n",
        "\n",
        "        resid_post = cache[f'blocks.{l}.hook_resid_post'][batch_idx]\n",
        "        mlp_contrib = (resid_post - resid_mid).cpu().numpy()\n",
        "\n",
        "        contributions['attn'].append(attn_contrib)\n",
        "        contributions['mlp'].append(mlp_contrib)\n",
        "        contributions['total'].append(attn_contrib + mlp_contrib)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return contributions\n",
        "\n",
        "contributions = compute_layer_contributions(cache, model)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "G-iB2spy86yR"
      },
      "execution_count": 127,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Geometric Alignment Between Layer Contributions\n",
        "\n",
        "For each layer $l$, we compute the cosine similarity between its total\n",
        "contribution $\\Delta x^{(l)}$ and the running residual stream before it:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\text{align}_l = \\cos\\left(\\Delta x^{(l)}, x^{(l-1)}\\right) = \\frac{\\Delta x^{(l)} \\cdot x^{(l-1)}}{\\|\\Delta x^{(l)}\\| \\|x^{(l-1)}\\|}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "This tells us: is layer $l$ pushing the residual stream in the same direction\n",
        "as the current state (constructive), opposite (destructive), or orthogonal\n",
        "(independent)?\n",
        "\"\"\""
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "F0qpFnHr-B8f"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def compute_alignments(contributions, cache, model, batch_idx=0):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Compute cosine similarities for geometric analysis.\"\"\"\n",
        "    n_layers = model.cfg.n_layers\n",
        "    alignments = {\n",
        "        'total_vs_pre': [], 'attn_vs_pre': [], 'mlp_vs_pre': [],\n",
        "        'attn_vs_mlp': [], 'consecutive_total': []\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "    for l in range(n_layers):\n",
        "        resid_pre = cache[f'blocks.{l}.hook_resid_pre'][batch_idx].cpu().numpy()\n",
        "\n",
        "        def batch_cosine(a, b):\n",
        "            dot = np.sum(a * b, axis=-1)\n",
        "            na = np.linalg.norm(a, axis=-1) + 1e-10\n",
        "            nb = np.linalg.norm(b, axis=-1) + 1e-10\n",
        "            return np.mean(dot / (na * nb))\n",
        "\n",
        "        alignments['total_vs_pre'].append(batch_cosine(contributions['total'][l], resid_pre))\n",
        "        alignments['attn_vs_pre'].append(batch_cosine(contributions['attn'][l], resid_pre))\n",
        "        alignments['mlp_vs_pre'].append(batch_cosine(contributions['mlp'][l], resid_pre))\n",
        "        alignments['attn_vs_mlp'].append(batch_cosine(contributions['attn'][l], contributions['mlp'][l]))\n",
        "\n",
        "        if l < n_layers - 1:\n",
        "            alignments['consecutive_total'].append(\n",
        "                batch_cosine(contributions['total'][l], contributions['total'][l+1]))\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            alignments['consecutive_total'].append(np.nan)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return alignments\n",
        "\n",
        "alignments = compute_alignments(contributions, cache, model)"
      ],
